article.headline: Utah Valley St. 77, S. Oregon 50
article.story: OREM, Utah -- Corey Claitt scored 18 points and made six assists to carry Utah State to a 77-50 win over Southern Oregon on Monday night. Claitt was one of five players to score double figures for the Wolverines (6-5), who pulled ahead just three minutes into the game and never trailed after that. Justin Baker added 13 for Utah Valley and Jordan Swarbrick scored 12, while Tyray Petty and Aaron England each picked up 11. Despite the Raiders (8-6) dropping their third game in a row, Humphrey Jackson led everyone in scoring with 20 points.
